Newcastle disease, Bulgaria
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 Nov 2016 from Dr Damyan Iliev, Chief Veterinary Officer & Deputy Executive Director, Bulgarian Food Safety Agency, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Sofia, Bulgaria

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 24 Oct 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 26 Oct 2016
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory basic
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Montana, Lom
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Oct 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 28 / 19 / 19 / 9 / 0
Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 67.86 / 67.86 / 100 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Source of the outbreak (s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Control measures: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestations; traceability; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; stamping out; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type/ Species / Test / Test date / Result
National reference laboratory (national laboratory) / Birds / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 26 Oct 2016 / Positive

Future reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Bulgaria suffered 3 outbreaks of Newcastle disease (NCD) earlier in 2016; the event started on 2 Feb 2016 and involved 3 outbreaks, of which 2 were in the southern province of Kardzali and one in its neighbor, Haskovo. Two of the outbreaks involved backyard holdings, while one involved a small commercial flock (676 susceptible birds, of which there were 15 cases/deaths). The event was declared as resolved on 18 Mar 2016.

An interactive OIE map showing the 3 Feb-March 2016 outbreaks, is available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=19705. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4603108,81.]
